DRIVING MISS DAISY 

Genres: Drama, Comedy 
Tagline: The comedy that won a Pulitzer Prize 
Plot Outline An old Jewish woman and her African-American chauffeur in the American South have a relationship that grows and improves over the years. 
Plot Synopsis: An elderly Jewish widow living in Atlanta can no longer drive. Her son insists she allow him to hire a driver, which in the 1950s meant a black man. She resists any change in her life but, Hoke, the driver is hired by her son. She refuses to allow him to drive her anywhere at first, but Hoke slowly wins her over with his native good graces. The movie is directly taken from a stage play and does show it. It covers over twenty years of the pair&amp;#039;s life together as they slowly build a relationship that transcends their differences. 
